<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4711251>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Johnsonita male forewing venation. A: J. auda left forewing membrane dissected and digitised; B: J. turquisca right forewing documented under optical miscroscope (arrow indicates the subcubital wrinkle) (in same magnification, scale as indicated)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4711251/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4711305>
    dc:description "FIGURE 23. Johnsonita mail trait ventral forewing subcubital scent patch indicated by arrow. A: J. carpia, B: J. catadupa, C: J. chlamydem, D: J. ianusca, E: J. johnsoni, F: J. pardoa, G: J. turquisca, H: J. zubkova." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4711305/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

